Academic Outcomes:
The main learning goals of this research project are:
* Understanding the intricacies of the current state of knowledge on scientific change;
* Mastering the diagrammatic notation and applying it to various belief systems;
* Understanding the team's role in the new digital workflow for piecemeal and transparent advancement of the field;
* Self-directed learning: acquiring necessary skills to conduct individual research in the field;
* Integration: connecting ideas in co-authored papers.

Student Roles:
Student will:
(1) read, summarise, and classify academic papers in computer systems education;
(2) find open courseware on computer systems, tabulate the concepts they cover, and classify the course (e.g., based on content, audience, etc.);
and (3) review student-centred tools used in computer systems education, attempt to use them, and reflect on the experience.
